The paper discusses succinct data structures, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The use of temporary extra buffers to store data during initialization is a technique that could be relevant to other areas of computer science, such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
